      <prop type="x-chinese-ref">易經 36 初九</prop>
      <prop type="x-translation-ref">易經 36 初九</prop>
      <tuv xml:lang="zh-Hant">
        <seg>初九：明夷于飛，垂其翼。君子于行，三日不食，有攸往，主人有言。</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv xml:lang="en">
        <seg>The first NINE, undivided, shows its subject, (in the condition indicated by) Ming Yi, flying, but with drooping wings. When the superior man (is revolving) his going away, he may be for three days without eating. Wherever he goes, the people there may speak (derisively of him).</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
