      <prop type="x-chinese-ref">易經 36 六二</prop>
      <prop type="x-translation-ref">易經 36 六二</prop>
      <tuv xml:lang="zh-Hant">
        <seg>六二：明夷，夷于左股，用拯馬壯，吉。</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv xml:lang="en">
        <seg>The second SIX, divided, shows its subject, (in the condition indicated by) Ming Yi, wounded in the left thigh. He saves himself by the strength of a (swift) horse; and is fortunate.</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
